The paper deals with lower bounds for space complexity in the streaming model, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The lower bound is obtained by analyzing a communication protocol for a variant of the Index function, which is a classic problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CGT) to obtain the lower bound. Finally, the paper briefly discusses quantum protocols for the same problem, which falls under the subfield of quantum information (cs.QI).
